[Algorithms] Two Fer Introduction Two-fer or 2-fer is short for two for one. One for you and one for me.
&#34;One for X, one for me.&#34; When X is a name or &ldquo;you&rdquo;.
If the given name is &ldquo;Alice&rdquo;, the result should be &ldquo;One for Alice, one for me.&rdquo;
If no name is given, the result should be &ldquo;One for you, one for me.&rdquo;
